(1, 'cell line: MCF-7Xx-xXcell type: weakly invasiveXx-xXtransfected with: si-RESTXx-xXgenotype/variation: Downregulation of REST', '1501 San Pablo St.', 'Los Angeles', 'USA', 'Biomedical Engineering', 'nanlee@usc.edu', 'University of Southern California', '', 'Nan,Sook,Lee', '6268243058', '90033', 'Bcl conversion: Illumina bcl2Fastq ver 1.8.4 to convert from bcl format to fastq.gz raw reads fileXx-xXAlignment and read counting done with GTFAR ver 0.1 using gencode19 annotation.Xx-xXA second alignment was done with Tophat ver 1.4.0 using hg19_ucsc reference and parameter -G hg19_ucsc.gtf (optional reference annotation)Xx-xXTranscript abundance estimation on the second alignment done with Cufflinks ver 1.0.1 using parameters -u (for multi-read-correct), -b hg19_ucsc.fa (for bias detection and correction) and -G hg19_ucsc.gtf (for optional reference annotation)Xx-xXGenome_build: hg19_ucscXx-xXSupplementary_files_format_and_content: tab-delimited text files from GT-FAR runs and Cufflinks runs which include RPKM values for each sample and isoform counts for each sample; more details in the \'README_1.txt\'', 0, '', 'Total RNAs were isolated from cell lines using Trizol (Invitrogen) and digested with Turbo DNase (Ambion) to remove genomic DNA, according to the manufacturer’s instructions.Xx-xXLibraries from rRNA-depleted samples were prepared using a TruSeq RNA Sample Preparation kit v2 (Illumina) following the recommended protocol starting from the RNA fragmentation stage. Purification of polyadenylated RNA was omitted. Libraries were pooled (4 samples per pool), clustered on cBOT (Illumina), and sequenced on HiSeq2000, each pool in one lane. We performed single-end 100 bp reads. Reads were mapped using TopHat followed by data analysis using Cufflinks and Cuffdiff software, as well as our own pipeline.', 'GSM1553456', 'Illumina HiSeq 2000', 'Dec 01 2014', 'cDNA', 'transcriptomic', 'RNA-Seq', 'total RNA', 'Homo sapiens', 'GPL11154', 'BioSample: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.g