ing criteria were used to : log2(fold change)>=1,  adj.p value < 0.0001,  exon bin size >= 100,  raw read counts >= 50  for at least one sample and gene expression is not significantly changed by compound treatment.Xx-xXTo identify pathways over-represented by genes whose splicing are changed by treatment, R package “GSEABase” (hypergeometric test) was used, adj.p.value (“BH”)  < 0.05, gene sets used was MSigDB canonical pathway collection C2.CP collection.Xx-xX‘Spliced Transcripts Alignment to a Reference (STAR)’ was used to align reads to human genome hg19 with default settingsXx-xXAll analyses were carried out using statistics software R (www.r-projects.org) unless stated otherwise.Xx-xXGenome_build: GRCh37.73Xx-xXSupplementary_files_format_and_content: Illumina', 0, '', 'RNeasy kit, Poly-A selection.Xx-xXStrand-specific RNA library construction were performed, followed by multiplexing indexed libraries and sequencing on the HiSeq 2500 with 2x100 bp read lengths', 'GSM3106217', 'Illumina HiSeq 2500', 'Apr 23 2018', 'cDNA', 'transcriptomic', 'RNA-Seq', 'total RNA', 'Homo sapiens', 'GPL16791', 'BioSample: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/biosample/SAMN08961954Xx-xXSRA: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sra?term=SRX3979816', 'GSE113426', 'Triple negative breast cancer (TNBC) line CAL51', 'Public on Apr 23 2018', 'Apr 20 2018', 'ftp://ftp.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/geo/samples/GSM3106nnn/GSM3106217/suppl/GSM3106217_DMSO_6hr_1-sortedByName-MarkDup.htseq-count.txt.gz', '', 9606, 'DMSO (6hr) - 1', 'SRA', 97017971, 104402994),
